class Solution {
    public String breakPalindrome(String palindrome) {
        int n = palindrome.length();
        if (n == 1) return "";
        char[] chars = palindrome.toCharArray();
        for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; i++) {
            if (chars[i] != 'a') {
                chars[i] = 'a';
                return new String(chars);
            }
        }
        chars[n - 1] = 'b';
        return new String(chars);
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the first half of the palindrome, replacing the first non-'a' character with 'a' to make the lexicographically smallest non-palindrome. If all characters are 'a', it replaces the last character with 'b' to make it non-palindromic.

